 {"id":"bd-2mvl","title":"Task: Implement mxbai-rerank-xsmall-v1 ONNX backend","description":"## Task: Implement mxbai-rerank-xsmall-v1 Backend

Integrate Mixedbread AI ultra-small reranker as an alternative to FlashRank.

## Model Details
- Source: mixedbread-ai/mxbai-rerank-xsmall-v1
- Parameters: ~100M (0.1B)
- Architecture: Cross-encoder optimized for speed
- Speed: ~15ms per query-doc pair on CPU
- Format: ONNX available via optimum export
- License: Apache-2.0
- Max sequence length: 512 tokens

## Why This Model
mxbai-rerank-xsmall sits between FlashRank nano (speed) and full cross-encoders (quality):
- 3x slower than FlashRank nano but significantly better quality
- Top-20 reranking: ~300ms (acceptable for CLI with daemon)
- ONNX-native, no Python dependency
- Same vendor as mxbai embedding models (potential synergy)

## Architecture
```rust
pub struct MxbaiReranker {
    session: ort::Session,
    tokenizer: tokenizers::Tokenizer,
    max_length: usize,       // 512 tokens
    batch_size: usize,       // 16 (smaller batches due to larger model)
    name: String,
}

impl Reranker for MxbaiReranker {
    fn rerank(&self, query: &str, documents: &[&str]) -> Result<Vec<f32>> {
        let mut all_scores = Vec::with_capacity(documents.len());

        for chunk in documents.chunks(self.batch_size) {
            // mxbai uses standard cross-encoder format:
            // [CLS] query_tokens [SEP] doc_tokens [SEP]
            let encodings: Vec<_> = chunk.iter()
                .map(|doc| self.tokenizer.encode((query, *doc), true)
                    .map(|e| e.truncate(self.max_length, 0)))
                .collect::<Result<Vec<_>>>()?;

            let max_len = encodings.iter().map(|e| e.len()).max().unwrap_or(0);

            // Build padded tensors
            let input_ids = build_padded_i64_tensor(&encodings, max_len);
            let attention_mask = build_attention_mask_i64(&encodings, max_len);

            // Run ONNX inference
            let outputs = self.session.run(ort::inputs![
                "input_ids" => input_ids,
                "attention_mask" => attention_mask,
            ]?)?;

            // mxbai-rerank outputs logits, apply sigmoid for [0,1] scores
            let logits = outputs[0].extract_tensor::<f32>()?;
            for i in 0..chunk.len() {
                all_scores.push(sigmoid(logits[[i, 0]]));
            }
        }

        Ok(all_scores)
    }

    fn model_name(&self) -> &str { &self.name }
    fn max_length(&self) -> usize { self.max_length }
}
```

